719314f-a.text:
Division Street, south side, east from but not including Catherine Street, to, but not including Market Street. No 7 Division Street, east of the S.E. corner of Division and Catherine Streets, is a 4-story frame house. The view shows the Second Ave., elevated overhead on
Division Street.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies, Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 587.

716730f-a.title: Manhattan: Bowery - Doyers Street
716730f-a.text:

1936.
Gift of Dr. Michael Wishengrad, A.R.P.S.

722539f.text:
Pell Street, west from a point opposite Doyers to Mott Streets, showing details of a portion of that Manhattan locality "Chinatown."
1939?
Alexander Alland
NEG # 1161
This photo is one of a series that appeared in the published volume "Portrait of N. Y." by Felix Reisenberg and Alex.
Alland, IRGV.
722539f.folder: Pell Street & Doyers Street, Manhattan, NY

722540f.text:
Pell Street, west from the head of Doyers Street, to Mott Street, showing street activity in New York's Chinatown. Note the co-mingling of the Occidental and the Oriental,
both in garb and advertising matter.
1940?
Alexander Alland, photo
NEG #710
